author: orlandosentinel.com
title: Hello Kitty Cafe Truck returns to Central Florida
text:
The Hello Kitty Cafe Truck will be making a return visit to Central Florida, bringing snacks and merchandise from the adorable Japanese cartoon character.
The Hello Kitty Cafe Truck will be at Altamonte Mall on March 4 from 10 a.m. to 8 p.m. The promotional food truck visited Florida Mall in October.
The mobile promotion sells food such as Hello Kitty Cookies, a rainbow maracon box and box-shaped boxes of water. It also has merchandise such as mugs, t-shirts and the charact’ers signature bow headband.
Central Florida is no stranger to Hello Kitty or merchandise. Hello Kitty’s parent company, Sanrio, opened an interactive Hello Kitty Shop at Universal Orlando in 2015.
The Hello Kitty Cafe Truck has two vehicles traveling across the country, one each on the East and West Coasts.
After the March 4 Altamonte appearance, the cafe truck will head north to Atlanta for a March 11 stop, and then to Charlotte on March 18.
There is also a Hello Kitty Cafe Pop-Up Container in Irvine, Calif.
